The march to clear the fleeing Boko Haram terrorists by the troops of the Nigerian Army is a task non-negotiable. Whether on land, air or water, the gallant troops have displayed an incredible desire to get rid of the already disseminated radical Islamic sect. This hunger, sacrifice and patriotism all came to the fore recently when the troops on the frontline delved into utterly toxic waters to defend the country against terrorism. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY From the Lake Chad river to the swamp of Sambisa, Damboa and Alagarno, the gallant officers went beyond the bounds for the greater good of the nation.   Buratai orders redeployment of troops to Lake Chad region Lake Chad no longer safe haven for B/Haram â€“ Buratai Troops neutralise over 100 Boko Haram terrorists, recover weapons